OL,3,C'Probable' patient would have survived
OL,4,Cwith different care, coroner says
OL,6,FThe coroner added that if Mr Watkins
OL,7,Fhad been sent to the hospital and the
OL,8,Fblood tests had been read when they
OL,9,Fwere first made available, 14 August
OL,10,Fat 8:16pm, then it is probable he
OL,11,Fwould have survived.
OL,13,FAndy Weir, the Director of Jersey's
OL,14,FMental Health and Adult Social Care
OL,15,Fdepartment, said: "We wish to
OL,16,Fsincerely apologise again to the
OL,17,Ffamily of Mr Watkins for the acts and
OL,18,Fomissions in his care and treatment.
